DAY-7

STRINGS IN JAVA

What is a String?

In Java, a **String**:

- Is a **sequence of characters**
- Is an **object**, not a primitive
- Is **immutable** (cannot be changed)

Example :

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void stringex() {
        String name = "prem thoke";
        System.out.println(name);
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        stringex();
    }
}
```

String vs char[]

| String | char[] |
| --- | --- |

| Immutable | Mutable |
| --- | --- |

| Many built-in methods | No built-in methods |
| --- | --- |

| Easy to use | Low-level |
| --- | --- |

Taking String Input

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void stringex() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter your name");
        String name = sc.nextLine();
        System.out.println("enter your age");
        int age = sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println("hello " + name);
        System.out.println("your " + age + " now that's cool");
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        stringex();
    }
}
```

Important String Methods - 

Length : s.length();
Character at index : s.charAt(0);
Substring : s.substring(1, 4);
Equals : s1.equals(s2); // correct  , s1 == s2; // wrong for string

To Upper / Lower  :  s.toUpperCase();  / s.toLowerCase();

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void stringex() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter your name");
        String name = sc.nextLine();
        String surname = "thoke";
        int len = name.length();
        char a = name.charAt(3);
        String subs = name.substring(1, 3);
        boolean eql = name.equals(surname);
        String upr = name.toUpperCase();
        String lwr = name.toLowerCase();
        System.out.println(len);
        System.out.println(a);
        System.out.println(subs);
        System.out.println(upr);
        System.out.println(lwr);
        System.out.println(eql);
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        stringex();
    }
}
```

Traversing a String :

```java
for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
    System.out.print(s.charAt(i) + " ");
}
```

String Immutability : This creates a **new String**, old one is untouched.

```java
String s = "hello";
s = s + " world";
```

Task1 - Take a string input - print its length , print each char on a new line

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void stringex() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter your name");
        String name = sc.nextLine();
        int len = name.length();
        System.out.println(len);
        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
            System.out.println(name.charAt(i));
        }
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        stringex();
    }
}
```

Task2 - Count how many **vowels** are in the String.

```
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void stringex() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter your name");
        String name = sc.nextLine();
        int len = name.length();
        char vowels[] = { 'a', 'e', 'o', 'i', 'u' };
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
            char ch = name.charAt(i);
            for (int j = 0; j < vowels.length; j++) {
                if (ch == vowels[j]) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }
        System.out.println(count);
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        stringex();
    }
}
```

Task3 - Reverse a string

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void stringex() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter your name");
        String name = sc.nextLine();
        int len = name.length();
        for (int i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            char ch = name.charAt(i);
            System.out.print(ch);
        }
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        stringex();
    }
}
```

Task4 - Palindrome 

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void stringex() {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("enter your name");
        String name = sc.nextLine();
        int len = name.length();
        String rev = "";
        for (int i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            rev = rev + name.charAt(i);
        }
        System.out.println(rev);
        if (name.equals(rev)) {
            System.out.println("palindrome");
        } else {
            System.out.println("not palindrome");
        }
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        stringex();
    }
}
```
